In [[mathematics]], the '''Laguerre form''' is generally given as a third degree [[tensor]]-valued form, that can be written as,

:<math>\mathfrak{L} = (w^{1})^{2} D a_{11} + 2 w^{1}w^{2} D a_{12} + (w^{2})^{2} D a_{22}</math>.

